# Project: {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Guidelines

- Use plan mode before implementing non-trivial changes
- Prefer subagents for parallel work — split independent tasks across agents
- When you hit an error, fix it autonomously — do not stop to ask
- Log every error and its fix to the learning pipeline
- Verify your work: run tests before marking any task as done
- Write concise commit messages focused on "what" and "why"
- Follow existing code conventions — check surrounding code before writing

## Testing

- Run `{{TEST_COMMAND}}` to verify all tests pass
- Tests must pass before any task transitions to "done"
- Write tests first (spec phase), then implement (execute phase)

## Code Style

- Match existing patterns in the codebase
- No unnecessary comments, docstrings, or type annotations on unchanged code
- Remove debug artifacts (console.log, TODO comments) before review
- Keep changes minimal and focused on the task

